<item>
            <title>[HIVE-5181] RetryingRawStore should not retry on logical failures (e.g. from commit)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-5181</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;RetryingRawStore retries calls. Some method (e.g. drop_table_core in HiveMetaStore) explicitly call openTransaction and commitTransaction on RawStore.&lt;br/&gt;
When the commit call fails due to some real issue, it is retried, and instead of a real cause for failure one gets some bogus exception about transaction open count.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I doesn&apos;t make sense to retry logical errors, especially not from commitTransaction.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
